message.content:
We start by gathering the key balances (all amounts are “End_amount” as of 2024-02-05):

1. From the balance sheet:
 • Current Assets = 21,224,639.20  
 • Inventory = 8,400,000.00  
 • Accounts Receivable = 10,221,447.35  
 • Current Liabilities = 727,140.68  
 • Total Assets = 29,133,140.32  
 • Total Owner’s Equity = 28,405,999.64  
 • (Total Liabilities = Total Assets – Owner’s Equity = 29,133,140.32 – 28,405,999.64 = 727,140.68)

2. From the cash flow statement:
 • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –17,417,367.15

3. From the income statement:
 • Main Business Revenue = 14,542,813.42  
 • Net Profit = 405,999.64

Now we calculate the ratios as follows:

────────────────────────────
1. Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio

 Formula: Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities

 = (–17,417,367.15) / (727,140.68)  
 ≈ –23.96  
 (we interpret the negative sign as the operating cash flow being negative relative to current liabilities)

────────────────────────────
2. Debt to Equity Ratio

 Formula: Total Liabilities / Owner’s Equity

 = 727,140.68 / 28,405,999.64  
 ≈ 0.0256  
 Rounded, we present this as 0.03

────────────────────────────
3. Total Asset Turnover Ratio

 Formula: Revenue / Total Assets

 = 14,542,813.42 / 29,133,140.32  
 ≈ 0.50

────────────────────────────
4. Quick Ratio

 Formula: (Current Assets – Inventory) / Current Liabilities

 = (21,224,639.20 – 8,400,000.00) / 727,140.68  
 = 12,824,639.20 / 727,140.68  
 ≈ 17.63

────────────────────────────
5. Operating Cash Flow Ratio

 This is typically the same as the operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio unless stated otherwise.

 Thus, it = –23.96

────────────────────────────
6. Return on Equity (ROE)

 Formula: Net Profit / Owner’s Equity

 = 405,999.64 / 28,405,999.64  
 ≈ 0.0143  → 1.43%

────────────────────────────
7. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio

 Formula: Revenue / Accounts Receivable

 = 14,542,813.42 / 10,221,447.35  
 ≈ 1.42

────────────────────────────
Now we present the final answers in the required JSON format:

{
  "solution": {
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-23.96",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.03",
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.50",
    "Quick Ratio": "17.63",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-23.96",
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "1.43%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "1.42"
  }
}
